Health Minister Zweli Mkhize has apologised for the disruptions caused by the Digital Vibes scandal. He says his intention is not to dodge questions but to make sure he fully cooperates with the SIU. #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG  - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize has apologised for the disruptions caused by the Digital Vibes scandal. He says his intention is not to dodge questions but to make sure he fully cooperates with the SIU. Mkhize says the matter has tainted the work being done to fight COVID-19. The Health Minister was in the Northern Cape on Tuesday where he visited various hospitals. READ: Mkhize denies saying probe is political The province recorded the highest number of infections in the country last week. It has also recorded 138 new cases overnight Watch the video above for more details on this story. Health Minister Mkhize says he takes full responsibility and apologises unreservedly for the outrage regarding the #DigitalVibes matter. #eNCA Health Minister Mkhize says he has played no role in the awarding of #DigitalVibes contract and he did not benefit from the contract in anyway. #eNCA Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says he has discussed special leave with President Cyril Ramaphosa. And when asked further on whether or not HE thinks HE should go on special leave, he said it’s being discussed with the President. #DigitalVibes